The global equity market selloff gathered significant momentum during the European session, sparking a strong flight-to-safety bid and spilling over to the South African bourse. The risk-off mood followed ongoing concerns about coronavirus second-wave infections as UK and European cases rise and the US death toll approaches 200,000. At the close of local trade, the rand quoted 3.52% weaker at R16.87/$, after trading in range of R16.25/$ - R16.94/$. The rand steadied overnight. Expected range today R16.50/$ - R17.00/$. --Iol--